After a small [survey on Reddit](https://www.reddit.com/r/cpp/comments/4izaxc/exception_design_use_default_exceptions_or/) it seems to be a good idea to replace the standard exceptions used in the library right now with user-defined exceptions.

The motivations for this are:
- Better differentiation between exceptions raised by the STL and those raised by the JSON library.
- Clearer semantics of the exceptions rather and the possibility of better diagnosis and documentation.

